Tool CreationUpdate — Overwrite VersionUpdate — Create New Version <p>When a tool is onboarded (<code>POST /tools/generate/onboard</code> or <code>POST /tools/upload</code>):</p> <ol> <li>Tool record is created in <code>tool_table</code></li> <li>Initial <code>v1</code> is created automatically in <code>tool_versions_table</code></li> <li>Python file is saved as <code>{tool_name}_v1.py</code></li> </ol> <p>To overwrite the code of an existing version:</p> <pre><code>{
  "version": "v1",
  "code_snippet": "..."
}
</code></pre> <p>Result: <code>v1</code> code is overwritten in place. No new version is created.</p> <p>To preserve the existing version and create a new one:</p> <pre><code>{
  "create_new_version": true,
  "code_snippet": "..."
}
</code></pre> <p>Result: New version created (e.g., <code>v2</code>, <code>v3</code>). Version number = <code>MAX(existing) + 1</code>. New file saved as <code>{tool_name}_{new_version}.py</code>.</p>

Delete VersionDelete ToolRestore Version <pre><code>DELETE /tools/{tool_id}?version=v2
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Check: Is this the last version? → Error if yes</li> <li>Get version data from <code>tool_versions_table</code></li> <li>Move to <code>recycle_tool_versions</code> (preserves all data)</li> <li>Delete from <code>tool_versions_table</code></li> <li>Delete file <code>{tool_name}_v2.py</code></li> </ol> <p>Info</p> <p>The version can be restored later from the recycle bin.</p> <pre><code>DELETE /tools/{tool_id}
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Check dependencies (agents using this tool)</li> <li>Move all versions to <code>recycle_tool_versions</code></li> <li>Move tool record to <code>recycle_tool</code> table</li> <li>Delete from <code>tool_table</code> (CASCADE deletes versions)</li> <li>Delete all version files</li> </ol> <p>Info</p> <p>The tool and all its versions can be restored together.</p> <pre><code>POST /tools/recycle-bin/versions/restore/{tool_id}/{version}
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Get version data from <code>recycle_tool_versions</code></li> <li>Check: Does version number already exist?<ul> <li>YES → Assign new version number (<code>MAX + 1</code>)</li> <li>NO → Use original version number</li> </ul> </li> <li>Create record in <code>tool_versions_table</code></li> <li>Recreate file <code>{tool_name}_{version}.py</code></li> <li>Delete from <code>recycle_tool_versions</code></li> </ol>
